          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI",
                "TELES",
                "SCIN",
                "GE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A silicon PIN diode telescope",
                "consisting of seven silicon detectors (each 50x50mm2),",
                "thick plastic scintillator, and germanium gamma-ray",
                "detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Rotating 8.0-mm-thick carbon target wheel",
                " (rho=1.89g/cm3)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The isotopes were created through the",
                "interaction of an 82Se beam with a carbon target. The",
                "production cross sections of neutron-rich nuclei were",
                "measured using the Advanced Rare Isotope Separator",
                " (ARIS). The event-by-event identification of each",
                "projectile-like reaction product was achieved through",
                "combined measurements of the magnetic rigidity (Brho),",
                "time of flight (ToF) from DB3 to DB5, energy",
                "loss (dE), and total kinetic energy (TKE)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The transmission analysis though ARIS separator using",
                "LISE++ was used to deduce production cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Uncertainties are separated into",
                "i) nuclide-dependent (point-to-point) systematic",
                "uncertainties associated with transmission/acceptance",
                "corrections and",
                "ii) correlated normalization (global) systematic",
                "uncertainties common to all nuclides.",
                "The transmission/acceptance component (angular,",
                "longitudinal, and wedge-selection efficiencies) was",
                "evaluated by varying relevant parameters over",
                "conservative ranges; the impact of wedge-material",
                "nonuniformity was included. Normalization systematics",
                " (e.g., beam integral, target thickness, and live-",
                "time/detector-efficiency terms) are not part of the",
                "transmission study and should be quoted/propagated as",
                "an overall scale uncertainty when provided."
              ]
            }
